sqDiagnosis_rule_amp_tip.description: {AMP rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_amp_tip.message:
AMP is a way to build web pages for static content that render fast.

AMP HTML is HTML with some restrictions for reliable performance and some extensions for building rich content beyond basic HTML.

You can check this [https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/6340290](Google support page) or [https://www.ampproject.org/docs/get_started/about-amp.html](AMP project guide).

sqDiagnosis_rule_analytics_tip.description: {Analytics rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_analytics_tip.message: Please follow this [https://moz.com/blog/absolute-beginners-guide-to-google-analytics](article) to get more information about Google Analytics

sqDiagnosis_rule_canonical_tip.description: {Canonical rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_canonical_tip.message: A canonical link tag is an HTML element that helps webmasters prevent duplicate content issues by specifying the ''canonical'' or ''preferred'' version of a webpage as part of search engine optimization.For more information, please see [https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/139066](this Google article).

sqDiagnosis_rule_doctype_tip.description: {Doctype rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_doctype_tip.message: Specifying a [http://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_DOCTYPE.asp](doctype) assists your web browser in correctly rendering your content.

sqDiagnosis_rule_encoding_tip.description: {Encoding rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_encoding_tip.message: Please follow this [https://www.w3.org/International/tutorials/tutorial-char-enc/](article) to find how to add proper character encoding to your site.

sqDiagnosis_rule_favicon_tip.description: {Favicon rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_favicon_tip.message:
Ensure that your favicon [http://www.howtojoomla.net/2007050865/how-tos/miscellaneous/how-to-change-your-favicon](reflects your brand).

Featured tip: If you want a better experience for your visitors, have a look at [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0KDjjePkd2U](this) great favicon.

sqDiagnosis_rule_flash_tip.description: {Flash rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_flash_tip.message:
Flash is only good in certain situations like enhancing the look of your page.

For better SEO, do not use flash at all.

It's possible that this could change in the near future but as of right now, Flash [http://www.beussery.com/blog/index.php/2008/10/google-flash-seo/](cannot be indexed) by search engines.

[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajax_%28programming%29](AJAX) is also in the [http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2009/10/proposal-for-making-ajax-crawlable.html](same category) as Flash.

sqDiagnosis_rule_frames_tip.description: {Frames ratio rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_frames_tip.message:
It's hard for search engines to index pages with frames since it does not follow [http://www.google.com/support/webmasters/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=34445](the standard layout for a website).

You should avoid the use of frames when optimizing your website.

sqDiagnosis_rule_headings_tip.description: {Headings rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_headings_tip.message:
You can include keywords in your headings.

The initial heading (<H1>) should include your best keywords.

Using only one <H1> heading per page will strengthen your SEO.

sqDiagnosis_rule_images_tip.description: {Images rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_images_tip.message:
We suggest adding ALT text to your images so that it's easier for search engines to index them.

Search engines don't physically see images the way people do. ALT text is an option that allows you to specifically describe the image.

ALT text attaches a description to your pictures so that they show up in [http://images.google.com/](Google™) and other search engine's image results.

Make sure your website images have their own [http://www.webcredible.co.uk/user-friendly-resources/web-accessibility/image-alt-text.shtml](specific ALT text).

To find out how to assign ALT text to your images, [http://www.seosmarty.com/image-seo/](click here).

Keep in mind that your pages load time will vary based on the number and size of your images. Try your best to keep it low.

Here’s a tip: You can see the past designs of any website by using [http://archive.org/web/](The Wayback Machine).

sqDiagnosis_rule_keywords_tip.description: {Meta keywords rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_keywords_tip.message: [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meta_element#The_keywords_attribute](Meta keywords) are words or phrases that pertain to your site's content. In the past, people have tried to take advantage of this tag so now it doesn't affect your search rankings the way that it used to.

sqDiagnosis_rule_language_tip.description: {Language rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_language_tip.message:
Here are some suggestions for multilingual sites:

⋅ You should declare the contents language in the HTML code of each page.
⋅ You should also declare the language code in the URL (for example: company.com/es/contact.html).
⋅ If you plan on building a multilingual site, refer to the tips found [http://www.toprankblog.com/2009/10/top-10-pitfalls-of-international-seo/](here)

sqDiagnosis_rule_meta_tip.description: {Meta description rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_meta_tip.message:
[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meta_element#The_description_attribute](Meta descriptions) are useful because they often dictate how your pages are shown in search results.

For optimum effectiveness, [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meta_element#The_description_attribute](meta descriptions) should be 160-300 characters long.

Your meta descriptions should be concise and contain your [http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2007/09/improve-snippets-with-meta-description.html](best keywords)

Make sure each page of your website has its own meta description.

sqDiagnosis_rule_microformats_tip.description: {Microformats rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_microformats_tip.message:
[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microformat](Microformat) is a markup that is used to structure the data that is being sent to search engines more effectively.

The presentation of Google's search results is always [http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2009/05/introducing-rich-snippets.html](improving) due to Microformats.

sqDiagnosis_rule_opengraph_tip.description: {Open Graph rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_opengraph_tip.message:
The Open Graph protocol enables any web page to become a rich object in a social graph. For instance, this is used on Facebook to allow any web page to have the same functionality as any other object on Facebook.

For more information, see [http://ogp.me/](The Open Graph protocol).

sqDiagnosis_rule_robots_tip.description: {Robots.txt rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_robots_tip.message:
This file restricts the activity of search engine crawlers and stops them from accessing certain pages and directories.

A [http://www.robotstxt.org/orig.html](robots.txt file) also locates the XML sitemap.

To check your robots.txt file for syntax errors, [https://www.google.com/webmasters/tools/robots-testing-tool](Click Here).

sqDiagnosis_rule_schemaorg_tip.description: {Schema.org rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_schemaorg_tip.message:
Using markup data on your webpages is a powerful way to increase your visibility to search engines and gain higher click-through rates, which may in turn lead to better rankings.

For more information, see [https://developers.google.com/search/docs/guides/intro-structured-data](Introduction to Structured Data).

sqDiagnosis_rule_sitemap_tip.description: {Meta viewport rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_sitemap_tip.message:
An [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sitemaps](XML sitemap) lists URLs that can be crawled and may offer other information such as how often you update, when your last update occurred and importance.

With an XML sitemap, search engines can index your website more accurately.

Although it's been [http://www.seomoz.org/blog/expert-advice-on-google-sitemaps-verify-but-dont-submit](debated), we suggest that you submit an XML sitemap to [http://www.google.com/webmasters/tools/](Google™ Webmasters Tools).

sqDiagnosis_rule_text2html_tip.description: {Text/HTML ratio rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_text2html_tip.message: The text to HTML ratio is not a direct ranking factor for search engines but there are many factors related to the ratio that indicate best SEO practices and thus may indirectly result in higher search rankings. Please follow this [https://www.woorank.com/en/blog/are-text-to-html-ratios-important](article) to get more information.

sqDiagnosis_rule_title_tip.description: {Title rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_title_tip.message:
The most effective page titles are about 10-70 characters long, including spaces.

Keep your titles concise and make sure they contain your [https://www.semrush.com/blog/seoquake-5-keys-to-optimizing-your-title-tags/?utm_source=seoquake&utm_medium=toolbar&utm_campaign=regular&ref=174537735](best keywords).

Each page should have its own exclusive title.

Featured tool: Here's a [http://www.seomofo.com/snippet-optimizer.html](snippet-optimizer) that allows you to see how your titles look on Google™ and other search results.

sqDiagnosis_rule_twittercard_tip.description: {Twitter card rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_twittercard_tip.message:
With Twitter Cards, you can attach rich photos, videos and media experience to Tweets that drive traffic to your website.

For more information, see [https://dev.twitter.com/cards/overview](Twitter documentation).

sqDiagnosis_rule_url_tip.description: {URL rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_url_tip.message:
Search engines and visitors can interact with your website more effectively when you use URLs that describe the pages content (for example: http://www.company.com/companyinformation).

URLs are extremely vital to your SEO campaign. Be sure to use URLs that make it [http://www.google.com/support/webmasters/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=147959](easy for Google™ to index your site).

Here's a suggestion: You can search for great domain names [http://instantdomainsearch.com/](here). If your desired name is not available, consider using [http://sedo.com](Sedo) to find an alternative.

When you trademark your domain name, it keeps other from stealing your brand.

sqDiagnosis_rule_viewport_tip.description: {Meta viewport rule tooltip. Can use some markdown for markup}
sqDiagnosis_rule_viewport_tip.message:
A viewport controls how a webpage is displayed on a mobile device. Without a viewport, mobile devices will render the page at a typical desktop screen width, scaled to fit the screen. Setting a viewport gives control over the page's width and scaling on different devices.

Please follow [https://developers.google.com/speed/docs/insights/ConfigureViewport](this article) to get more information about viewport.

sqGSC_domain_score_tooltip.message: This metric measures the importance of a domain using a 100-point scale (from 0 to 100) and is based on the quality and volume of links pointing to this domain. The higher the score, the higher the quality of the domain. Domain Score is calculated in the same way as Google's PageRank

sqGSC_onboarding_notes_text.message:
*Welcome Notes for Google algorithm updates*

Keep up to date with Google algorithm updates. With the Notes feature enabled, you will see information about Google updates directly in Google Search Console charts.

sqGSC_onboarding_text.message:
*Meet the domain’s Volume and Trust metrics!*

These metrics allow you to easily estimate the importance and trustworthiness of a particular domain based on the number and quality of the backlinks pointing to it.

sqGSC_trust_score_tooltip.message: This metric measures the trustworthiness of a particular domain using a 100-point scale (with ‘0’ indicating a low-trust site and ‘100’ indicating a highly trusted site) and is based on the number of backlinks from trusted sites pointing to the domain. If a site’s Trust Score is significantly lower than its Domain Score, this may be a sign that the latter was artificially inflated. Backlinks from such sites may trigger Google penalties.

sqSERPSemRush_connect_block.message: Get *domain authority*, *visits* and *engagement data* with a free SEMrush account - [#connect](Connect)

sqSERPSemRush_hint.message:
*Domain Score* is a metric that measures the quality and volume of links pointing to the domain. The closer the score is to 100, the higher the quality of the domain.

*Trust Score* is a similar metric, used to measure the trustworthiness of a domain based on how many trusted backlinks the domain has. If the Trust Score is significantly lower than the Domain Score, it may be a sign that the domain has a high amount of untrustworthy backlinks.

sqSERPSemRush_onboarding_text.message:
*Meet Domain Authority and Engagement data!*

*Domain authority* metrics allow you to estimate the importance and trustworthiness of a website based on the number and quality of backlinks it has.

*Visits and user engagement* metrics provide insights into any website’s online presence and audience behavior.
